objects.name: locationjuan
objects.string:
2045… Location: Milky Way, Terrestrial Quadrant
Status: Alive
Mission: Deliver samples to space colonies

objects.name: NewText
objects.string:
Binnacle entry #001, Mission J.U.A.N, October 9th, 2045: 
The Spacecraft has left the upper terrestrial atmosphere and is now headed towards deep space, marking the beginning of our 5 year journey to reach Juanopolis International Space Colony. NASA has been actively working alongside various associations to study the effects of deep space stresses on different organisms. We must bring these samples to colonies in outer space for further research.

objects.name: sampleRoomTexto
objects.string:
Head to the SAMPLE ROOM and 
study the samples’ capabilities. 
Some of them should come in handy…
Use the keys A and D to walk to the Sample Room.

objects.name: entering
objects.string: You are entering to Sample Room

objects.name: txtCapMise
objects.string:
CAPSULA MISE
Species Name: Mus musculus
Field of Research: Radiation
Capabilities: Radiation resistance up to 9 grays for prolonged periods of time. Research focused on survival capabilities in hostile environments. These mice are trained to follow simple instructions. Wonder how could we use that for our advantage?

objects.name: txtMossPiglets
objects.string:
CAPSULA MOSS PIGLETS :
Species Name: Tardigrades
Field of Research: Endurance
Capabilities: Radiation resistance up to 6,000 grays for 
prolonged periods of time. Temperature resistance in mortally
cold and hot environments.

objects.name: txtCapsulaGragon
objects.string:
CAPSULA DRAGONFLIES: 
Species Name: Anisoptera
Field of Research: Sight
Capabilities: 360° sight range.
 Appliances to be defined.

objects.name: txtCapsulaBees
objects.string:
CAPSULA BEES: 
Species Name: Anthophila
Field of Research: Sight
Capabilities: Electromagnetic spectrum widening. Able to see in ultraviolet and infrared light.

objects.name: txtCapsulaPotatoes
objects.string:
CAPSULA POTATOES: 
Species Name: Solanum Tuberosun
Field of Research: Means of sustenance 
Capabilities: Growth in unvirtuous environments. Easiest nourishment to obtain in outer space.

eventsFunctionsExtensions.author: westboy, daliyoucefmedakram@gmail.com, @bouh
eventsFunctionsExtensions.description:
Animate text to simulate it being written one character at at time (a "typewriter" effect), with a customizable time between each character. Useful for dialogue scenes or visual novels.

How to use:
- Add the behavior to a Text object (BBText, Bitmap Text object) and choose the interval between characters.

Tips:
- Change the typing speed with the "Change interval" action.
- Pause the typing and resume it at any time.
- Use the "Skip to end of text" action to give users a way to skip text they don't want to read 
- If the text changes, the automatic typing starts again from the beginning with the new text.
- Use a condition to check if the typing finished.
- Use a condition to check if a new text character was added. This is useful to trigger audio effects.
- Use the "CurrentCharacter" expression to know when a specific character was displayed.
eventsFunctionsExtensions.fullName: Auto typing animation for text ("typewriter" effect)

eventsFunctionsExtensions.author: 4ian
eventsFunctionsExtensions.description: Behaviors to animate Tiled Sprite objects in the background, following the camera with a parallax effect.
eventsFunctionsExtensions.name: Parallax
eventsFunctionsExtensions.shortDescription: Behaviors to animate Tiled Sprite objects in the background, following the camera with a parallax effect.

eventsBasedBehaviors.description: Move the image of a Tiled Sprite to follow the camera horizontally with a parallax effect. After adding this to an object, put the object on a layer that is not moving, behind the layer that is followed (for example, a layer called "Background").
eventsBasedBehaviors.fullName: Horizontal Parallax for a Tiled Sprite
eventsBasedBehaviors.name: HorizontalTiledSpriteParallax

propertyDescriptors.label: Parallax factor (speed for the parallax, usually between 0 and 1)
propertyDescriptors.name: ParallaxFactor

propertyDescriptors.label: Layer to be followed (leave empty for the base layer)
propertyDescriptors.name: FollowedLayer

eventsBasedBehaviors.description: Move the image of a Tiled Sprite to follow the camera vertically with a parallax effect. After adding this to an object, put the object on a layer that is not moving, behind the layer that is followed (for example, a layer called "Background").
eventsBasedBehaviors.fullName: Vertical Parallax for a Tiled Sprite
eventsBasedBehaviors.name: VerticalTiledSpriteParallax

propertyDescriptors.label: Parallax factor (speed for the parallax, usually between 0 and 1)
propertyDescriptors.name: ParallaxFactor

propertyDescriptors.label: Layer to be followed (leave empty for the base layer)
propertyDescriptors.name: FollowedLayer
